<doc id="113105" wikidata="Q243384" url="?curid=113105" title="542 BC">
<text>The year 542 BC was a year of the pre-Julian Roman calendar. In the Roman Empire, it was known as year 212 &quot; [[Ab urbe condita]]&quot;. The denomination 542 BC for this year has been used since the early medieval period, when the Anno Domini calendar era became the prevalent method in Europe for naming years.

==Events==
Jambuswami; the head of the Jain order for 44 years after the Nirvan of Mahaveer Swami, attained Nirvan at the age of 80 years old. 

