<text>The year 534 BC was a year of the pre-Julian Roman calendar. In the Roman Empire, it was known as year 220 &quot; [[Ab urbe condita]]&quot;. The denomination 534 BC for this year has been used since the early medieval period, when the Anno Domini calendar era became the prevalent method in Europe for naming years.

